Path: This Week in Nushell #320
Content:




Published Wednesday, 2025-11-19, including PRs merged Friday, 2025-10-03 through Thursday, 2025-10-09.
íŔ@6b383841c809a13f7114f8d7661f5b30d1bb0debe4caff54e5bfcc477e2633aaŕxTitle: title: 'This week in Nushell #320'
Path: Nushell
Content:
@cablehead:
[link: #16836] fixed HTTP/metadata access examples requiring '--allow-errors' flag
[link: #16821] added custom metadata support and HTTP response metadata
@Bahex:
[link: #16835] removed 
``pipeline``
 calls added after testing refactor branched off
[link: #16820] marked 
``Value``
 variants as 
``#[non_exhaustive]``
[link: #16818] increased timeout for 
``hover_on_external_command``
[link: #16817] added tests for ast-grep rules
[link: #16810] made 
``compact``
 work on records
[link: #16802] completed big testing refactor
[link: #16789] added syntax for simple completions from const lists
[link: #16765] implemented command-wide completions
[link: #16735] enabled 
``each``
 to flatten streams from closures without collecting
@app/dependabot:
[link: #16824] bumped shadow-rs from 1.3.0 to 1.4.0
[link: #16823] bumped rmcp from 0.7.0 to 0.8.1
@ayax79:
[link: #16819] cleaned up Polars input/output types
@Tyarel8:
[link: #16809] added cell-path input to 
``into string``
@132ikl:
[link: #16799] removed all usages of 
``internal_span``
[link: #16770] added 
``run pr``
 and 
``download pr``
 to 
``toolkit``
@fdncred:
[link: #16791] updated reedline to latest commit
@nome:
[link: #16775] fixed Windows device paths
@Xylobyte:
[link: #16681] escaped markdown characters for valid table output and added new switches
